text_answer.content: I would like to see a more specific sample answer and evaluation for Short Answer #1. The question is about aging becoming a global challenge. The answer should reflect more appropriately the "global" part of it. Instead of just saying "many countries are already changing...", we should ask for more specific information. We reference both Japan and northern Europe and should encourage a reference using one of those countries, for example. The evaluation portion is just too vague. I love the writing prompt, however. It is creative and the passage lends itself to many ideas for this writing prompt.

text_answer.content: While this passage is appropriate for 7th grade, it is a somewhat difficult poem to understand. Many 7th graders have not been exposed to much poetry, and this poem could be difficult for a 7th grader to follow. The metaphors could be hard for them to follow. Also, some of the language used ("lips unused to thee", "and is lost in balms") will not be very obvious to this age. Please place it late in the curriculum if we are keeping it in here.
